        <%= image_tag "python.png", class: "img-responsive center-block" %>
  	    <p class="top-buffer-large">Python is ideal if you’re curious about programming. It is widely regarded as the best programming language for beginners for some good reasons. The language has a beautiful and clean-looking syntax that reads a lot like normal English, so it’s easy to understand the basic concepts.</p>
  		  <p>Python is a general-purpose language that runs on different platforms and can be used in a lot of different fields from science to web application development. Chances are therefore high that you can use Python for your first real world project even if you don’t know yet what kind of application you are going to build. A wide range of free Python libraries allows you to write useful real world applications even at beginner stage.</p>
        <p>Last but not least, Python is tremendously well documented and there’s an enthusiastic online community which can offer help and support if you ever get stuck. Applications built with Python include YouTube, Instagram and Spotify.</p>
      </div>
